WEBVTT

00:18.840 --> 00:23.360
CHAPTER XVII. A NEW INTEREST IN LIFE

00:23.720 --> 00:27.300
The next afternoon Anne, bending over her patchwork at the kitchen

00:27.300 --> 00:33.180
happened to glance out and beheld Diana down by the diet's bubble beckoning mysteriously.

00:33.720 --> 00:37.040
In a trice Anne was out of the house and flying down the hollow,

00:37.620 --> 00:40.440
astonishment and hope struggling in her expressive eyes.

00:40.860 --> 00:44.080
But the hope faded when she saw Diana's dejected countenance.

00:44.520 --> 00:47.180
Your mother hasn't relented? she gasped.

00:47.420 --> 00:49.100
Diana shook her head mournfully.

00:49.600 --> 00:53.480
No, and oh, Anne, she says I'm never to play with you again.

00:53.640 --> 00:56.520
I've cried and cried and I told her it wasn't your fault,

00:56.520 --> 00:57.980
but it wasn't any use.

00:58.260 --> 01:02.440
I had ever such a time coaxing her to let me come down and say goodbye to you.

01:02.740 --> 01:06.360
She said I was only to stay ten minutes and she's timing me by the clock.

01:07.340 --> 01:12.140
Ten minutes isn't very long to say an eternal farewell in, said Anne tearfully.

01:12.740 --> 01:16.160
Oh, Diana, will you promise faithfully never to forget me,

01:16.220 --> 01:19.720
the friend of your youth, no matter what dearer friends may caress thee?

01:21.020 --> 01:25.660
Indeed I will, sobbed Diana, and I'll never have another bosom friend.

01:25.660 --> 01:27.060
I don't want to have.

01:27.360 --> 01:29.660
I couldn't love anybody as I love you.

01:30.280 --> 01:33.400
Oh, Diana, cried Anne, clasping her hands.

01:33.760 --> 01:35.120
Do you love me?

01:36.460 --> 01:37.900
Why, of course I do.

01:38.080 --> 01:39.300
Didn't you know that?

01:40.000 --> 01:42.960
No, Anne drew a long breath.

01:43.800 --> 01:47.420
I thought you liked me, of course, but I never hoped you loved me.

01:47.800 --> 01:50.680
Why, Diana, I didn't think anybody could love me.

01:51.020 --> 01:53.720
Nobody ever has loved me since I can remember.

01:53.720 --> 01:55.500
Oh, this is wonderful.

01:55.860 --> 01:59.800
It's a ray of light which will forever shine on the darkness of the path,

01:59.980 --> 02:01.340
severed from thee, Diana.

02:01.720 --> 02:03.320
Oh, just say it once again.

02:04.080 --> 02:07.860
I love you devotedly, Anne, said Diana staunchly,

02:07.940 --> 02:09.460
and I always will.

02:09.600 --> 02:11.120
You may be sure of that.

02:11.960 --> 02:17.920
And I will always love thee, Diana, said Anne solemnly extending her hand.

02:18.440 --> 02:22.820
In the years to come, thy memory will shine like a star

02:22.820 --> 02:27.280
over my lonely life, as that last story we read together says.

02:27.840 --> 02:32.200
Diana, wilt thou give me a lock of thy jet-black tresses

02:32.200 --> 02:34.900
imparting to treasure forevermore?

02:36.000 --> 02:37.760
Have you got anything to cut it with?

02:37.940 --> 02:42.500
queried Diana, wiping away the tears which Anne's affecting accents

02:42.500 --> 02:46.160
had caused to flow fresh and returning to practicalities.

02:46.980 --> 02:51.980
Yes, I've got my patchwork scissors in my apron pocket, fortunately, said Anne.

02:51.980 --> 02:55.120
She solemnly clipped one of Diana's curls.

02:56.040 --> 02:58.500
Fare thee well, my beloved friend.

02:59.060 --> 03:02.820
Henceforth we must be as strangers, though living side by side,

03:03.060 --> 03:06.060
but my heart will ever be faithful to thee.

03:07.240 --> 03:09.840
Anne stood and watched Diana out of sight,

03:10.340 --> 03:13.620
mournfully waving her hand to the latter whenever she turned to look.

03:14.400 --> 03:16.320
Then she returned to the house,

03:16.660 --> 03:20.300
not a little consoled for the time being by this romantic parting.

03:22.220 --> 03:25.680
It's all over, she informed Marilla.

03:26.200 --> 03:28.260
I shall never have another friend.

03:28.820 --> 03:30.660
I'm really worse off than ever before,

03:30.800 --> 03:33.380
for I haven't Katie Morris and Violetta now.

03:34.340 --> 03:36.840
And even if I had, it wouldn't be the same.

03:37.380 --> 03:41.980
Somehow little dream girls are not satisfying after a real friend.

03:42.840 --> 03:46.300
Diana and I had such an affecting farewell down by the spring.

03:46.640 --> 03:49.140
It will be sacred in my memory forever.

03:49.140 --> 03:52.640
I used the most pathetic language I could think of and said,

03:53.000 --> 03:57.520
Thou and thee. Thou and thee seem so much more romantic than you.

03:58.380 --> 03:59.980
Diana gave me a lock of her hair,

04:00.020 --> 04:04.440
and I'm going to sew it up in a little bag and wear it around my neck all my life.

04:05.120 --> 04:09.320
Please see that it is buried with me, for I don't believe I'll live very long.

04:09.780 --> 04:13.680
Perhaps when she sees me lying cold and dead before her,

04:13.820 --> 04:16.740
Mrs. Berry might feel remorse for what she has done

04:16.740 --> 04:19.180
and will let Diana come to my funeral.

04:20.620 --> 04:24.460
I don't think there is much fear of your dying of grief,

04:24.760 --> 04:28.840
as long as you can talk, Anne, said Marilla unsympathetically.

04:29.480 --> 04:33.540
The following Monday, Anne surprised Marilla by coming down from her room

04:33.540 --> 04:38.740
with her basket of books on her arm and hip and her lips primmed up into a line of determination.

04:39.460 --> 04:41.820
I am going back to school, she announced.

04:42.160 --> 04:44.500
That is all that is left in life for me,

04:44.500 --> 04:47.460
now that my friend has been ruthlessly torn from me.

04:47.800 --> 04:50.840
In school I can look at her and muse over days departed.

04:51.840 --> 04:56.280
You had better muse over your lessons and sums, said Marilla,

04:57.020 --> 04:59.940
concealing her delight at this development of the situation.

05:00.580 --> 05:04.880
If you are going back to school, I hope we'll hear no more of breaking slates

05:04.880 --> 05:10.840
over people's heads and such careings on. Behave yourself and do just what your teacher tells you.

05:11.980 --> 05:15.240
I'll try to be a model pupil, agreed Anne dolefully.

05:16.160 --> 05:17.920
There won't be much fun in it, I expect.

05:18.600 --> 05:21.840
Mr. Phillips said Minnie Andrews was a model pupil,

05:21.960 --> 05:24.860
and there isn't a spark of imagination or life in her.

05:25.120 --> 05:29.080
She is just dull and pokey and never seems to have a good time.

05:29.580 --> 05:33.280
But I feel so depressed that perhaps it will come easy to me now.

05:33.860 --> 05:35.580
I'm going round by the road.

05:35.840 --> 05:38.880
I couldn't bear to go by the birch path all alone.

05:38.880 --> 05:41.740
I should weep bitter tears if I did.

05:44.280 --> 05:47.060
Anne was welcomed back to school with open arms.

05:47.380 --> 05:51.360
Her imagination had been sorely missed in games, her voice in the singing,

05:51.560 --> 05:55.460
and her dramatic ability in the perusal or loud of books at dinner hour.

05:56.120 --> 06:00.420
Ruby Gillis smuggled three blue plums over to her during testament reading.

06:01.000 --> 06:07.000
Ella MacPherson gave her an enormous yellow pansy cut from the covers of a floral catalogue,

06:07.000 --> 06:10.820
a species of desk decoration much prized in Evanley School.

06:11.840 --> 06:16.700
Sophia Sloan offered to teach her a perfectly elegant new pattern of knit lace,

06:17.120 --> 06:19.080
so nice for trimming aprons.

06:19.600 --> 06:23.360
Katie Bolter gave her a perfume bottle to keep slate water in.

06:24.040 --> 06:28.140
And Julia Bell copied carefully on a piece of pale pink paper

06:28.140 --> 06:30.420
scalloped on the edges the falling effusion.

06:31.100 --> 06:35.180
When twilight drops her curtain down and pins it with a star,

06:35.180 --> 06:38.700
remember that you have a friend, though she may wander far.

06:40.020 --> 06:45.040
It is so nice to be appreciated, sighed Anne rapturously to Marilla that night.

06:46.520 --> 06:49.820
The girls were not the only scholars who appreciated her.

06:50.380 --> 06:52.700
When Anne went to her seat after dinner hour,

06:52.900 --> 06:56.640
she had been told by Mr. Phillips to sit with the model Minnie Andrews.

06:56.820 --> 07:00.300
She found on her desk a big luscious strawberry apple.

07:00.980 --> 07:04.300
Anne cut it up all ready to take a bite when she remembered

07:04.300 --> 07:07.820
that the only place in Evanley where strawberry apples grew

07:07.820 --> 07:13.280
was in the old Blythe Orchard on the other side of Lake of Shining Waters.

07:14.340 --> 07:17.240
Anne dropped the apple as if it were a red-hot coal

07:17.240 --> 07:20.780
and ostentatiously wiped her fingers on her handkerchief.

07:21.960 --> 07:25.100
The apple lay untouched on her desk until the next morning

07:25.100 --> 07:30.000
when little Timothy Andrews, who swept the school and kindled the fire,

07:30.260 --> 07:32.060
annexed it as one of his prerequisites.

07:33.260 --> 07:39.860
Charlie Sloane's slate pencil, gorgeously bedizened with striped red and yellow paper,

07:40.340 --> 07:44.240
costing two cents, where ordinary pencils cost only one,

07:44.720 --> 07:49.140
which he sent up to her after dinner hour, met with a more favourable reception.

07:50.100 --> 07:54.620
Anne was graciously pleased to accept it and rewarded the donor with a smile,

07:54.960 --> 07:59.880
which exalted that infatuated youth straight away into the seventh heaven of delight,

08:00.520 --> 08:04.020
and caused him to make such fearful errors in his dictation

08:04.020 --> 08:07.020
that Mr. Phillips kept him in after school to rewrite it.

08:07.780 --> 08:11.680
But as the Caesar's pageants, shorn of Brutus Bus,

08:11.960 --> 08:14.880
did but of Rome's best son remind her more.

08:15.640 --> 08:19.700
So the market absent of any tribute or recognition from Diana Barry,

08:19.800 --> 08:23.760
who was sitting with Gertie Pyle, embittered Anne's little triumph.

08:25.040 --> 08:30.040
"'Diana might just have smiled at me once, I think,' she mourned to Marilla that night.

08:30.720 --> 08:35.980
The next morning a note most fearfully and wonderfully twisted and folded

08:35.980 --> 08:38.820
and a small parcel were passed across to Anne.

08:39.540 --> 08:41.280
"'Dear Anne,' ran the former,

08:41.460 --> 08:45.660
"'Mother says I'm not to play with you or talk to you even in school.

08:45.840 --> 08:50.220
It isn't my fault, and don't be cross at me because I love you as much as ever.

08:50.220 --> 08:56.440
I miss you awfully to tell all my secrets to, and I don't like Gertie Pyle one bit.

08:57.120 --> 09:00.340
I made one of the new bookmarkers out of red tissue paper.

09:00.700 --> 09:05.380
They are awfully fashionable now, and only three girls in school know how to make them.

09:05.860 --> 09:09.820
When you look at it, remember your true friend, Diana Barry.'

09:11.560 --> 09:15.800
Anne read the note, kissed the bookmark, and dispatched a prompt reply

09:15.800 --> 09:17.560
back to the other side of the school.

09:18.680 --> 09:24.840
"'My own darling Diana, of course I am not cross at you because you have to obey your mother.

09:25.340 --> 09:29.760
Our spirits can commune. I shall keep your lovely present forever.

09:30.520 --> 09:34.360
Minnie Andrews is a very nice little girl, although she has no imagination.

09:34.820 --> 09:38.920
But after having been Diana's bosom friend, I cannot be Minnie's.

09:39.780 --> 09:44.660
Please excuse mistakes, as my spelling isn't very good yet, although much improved.

09:45.300 --> 09:50.400
Yours until death us do part, Anne or Cordelia, surely.

09:51.400 --> 09:56.780
P.S. I shall sleep with your letter under my pillow tonight, A or C.S.'

09:59.880 --> 10:04.780
Marilla pessimistically expected more trouble since Anne had again begun to go to school,

10:05.100 --> 10:09.300
but none developed. Perhaps Anne caught something of the

10:09.940 --> 10:15.100
from Minnie Andrews. At least she got on very well with Mr. Phillips thenceforth.

10:15.740 --> 10:21.800
She flung herself into her study's heart and soul, determined not to be outdone in any class by

10:21.800 --> 10:27.920
Gilbert Blythe. The rivalry between them was soon apparent. It was entirely good-natured

10:27.920 --> 10:32.860
on Gilbert's side, but it is much to be feared that the same thing cannot be said of Anne,

10:32.980 --> 10:36.940
who had certainly an unpraised worthy tenacity for holding grudges.

10:37.700 --> 10:43.820
She was as intense in her hatreds as in her loves. She would not stoop to admit that she

10:43.820 --> 10:48.760
meant to rival Gilbert in schoolwork, because that would have been to acknowledge his existence,

10:48.980 --> 10:55.500
which Anne persistently ignored. But the rivalry was there, and honours fluctuated between them.

10:56.060 --> 11:01.980
Now Gilbert was head of the spelling class, now Anne, with a toss of her long red braids,

11:01.980 --> 11:08.260
spelled him down. One morning Gilbert had all his sums done correctly and had his name written on

11:08.260 --> 11:14.540
the blackboard on the roll of honour. The next morning Anne, having wrestled wildly with

11:14.540 --> 11:20.860
decimals the entire evening before, would be first. One awful day they were ties,

11:21.240 --> 11:26.100
and their names were written up together. It was almost as bad as a take notice,

11:26.100 --> 11:30.800
and Anne's mortification was as evident as Gilbert's satisfaction.

11:31.800 --> 11:36.680
When the written examinations at the end of each month were held, the suspense was terrible.

11:37.200 --> 11:43.580
The first month, Gilbert came out three marks ahead. The second, Anne beat him by five. But

11:43.580 --> 11:48.800
her triumph was marred by the fact that Gilbert congratulated her heartily before the whole school.

11:49.320 --> 11:53.800
It would have been ever so much sweeter to her if he had felt the sting of his defeat.

11:53.800 --> 12:01.280
Mr. Phillips might not be a very good teacher, but a pupil so inflexibly determined on learning

12:01.280 --> 12:05.740
as Anne was, could hardly escape making progress under any kind of teacher.

12:06.560 --> 12:12.000
By the end of term, Anne and Gilbert were both promoted into the fifth class and allowed to

12:12.000 --> 12:18.160
begin studying the elements of the branches, by which Latin, Geometry, French and Algebra were

12:18.980 --> 12:21.980
In geometry, Anne met her Waterloo.

12:22.920 --> 12:30.640
It's perfectly awful stuff, Marilla, she groaned. I'm sure I'll never be able to make head or

12:30.640 --> 12:37.440
tail of it. There is no scope for imagination in it at all. Mr. Phillips says I'm the worst

12:37.440 --> 12:43.920
dunce he ever saw at it, and Gil, I mean some of the others, are so smart at it. It is extremely

12:43.920 --> 12:50.680
mortifying, Marilla. Even Diana gets along better than I do, but I don't mind being beaten by Diana.

12:51.460 --> 12:55.220
Even though we meet as strangers now, I still love her with an

12:56.020 --> 13:00.300
inextinguishable love. It makes me very sad at times to think about her.

13:01.160 --> 13:06.800
But really, Marilla, one can't stay sad very long in such an interesting world can one?

13:13.920 --> 13:17.360
February 11, 2006

